ACT:
 Indian Penal Code, 1860: ss. 201 & 302-Murder- Conviction based on circumstancial evidence-Held, charge not proved beyond doubt.
 Evidence Act, 1872: ss. 24 & 27: Extrajudicial confession-No corroborative evidence-Held, very weak piece of evidence-Dead bodies-Recovery of from open field-Held, exclusive knowledge cannot be attributed to the accused- Consequently evidence under s. 27 cannot be a circumstance against the accused.
 
